content: Maximum Africa L.E.O Group, we are driven by a fervent dedication to nurturing innovation, supporting Business Leaders, and facilitating connections with investors seeking high-impact opportunities. Our deep-rooted understanding of the intricacies and potential of the African market has enabled us, to curate a dynamic ecosystem that fosters partnership and collaboration, by providing rigorous vetting, personalized support, and strategic networking opportunities. With an unwavering commitment to excellence and success, Maximum Africa L.E.O opens doors to lucrative prospects where innovation seamlessly intertwines with Maximum luxury, Entrepreneurship and Opportunities, catalyzing Africa’s economic transformation. Romeo Manyika and Slaven Gajović are the chairman and founders of Maximum Africa L.E.O Romeo is an Industrialist, a serial Entrepreneur, Angel investor and Dealmaker. Romeo is the current CEO at AFRICA L.E.O (Luxury, Entrepreneurship & Opportunities) PRIVATE MEMBERS BUSINESS

Transaction advisory & management. Acts as an Overseer Principal for investment houses which specializes in financing projects in the emerging markets and frontier economies. He has solid networks of other investors of global capital plus providers of investment advisory and government services which he can tap into on behalf of clients. Based on his career experience in frontier markets and academic expertise in Finance and Economics, he has the following core competencies: Geographic Knowledge of Frontier Markets: He has either lived, worked or visited extensively in frontier markets, especially sub-Saharan Africa, Middle-East, Europe, including c75 field research trips to these states

for over a decade. An Extensive & High Profile Network of Contacts: This ensures ready and efficient access to key decision makers in frontier markets in the government, corporate, banking and Development Finance Institutions (DFI) sectors. Product Knowledge of Global Investment Banking: Origination, Structuring and Distribution of assets from frontier markets to global investors; Trading a frontier market FX, fixed finance income and credit derivative client and proprietary book; Fund Managing frontier market multi- asset portfolios including FX, fixed income and equities. Market Intelligence & International Investor Access: Either through personal network or via best-in-class distribution agents to ensure that assets are targeted to investors with a proven and repeatable risk appetite for frontier market exposure. Slaven Gajović wasBorn 1972 in Belgrade, the capital city of Serbia, where in 1991 Slaven finished schooling and obtained a diploma in IT (qualified computer programmer) w

ith distinction. Thereafter, Slaven started at a paging company where, within a few months, was promoted to Pager Programming Department Manager. Due to the political situation, he decided to emigrate and chose South Africa as the destination. Slaven arrived in SA in 1992 and started pursuing a computer career. In 1993 he found an interest in real estate investments and the same year founded his first Real Estate company. Since then Slaven has tweaked interests to commercial and Mega Project Property Developments as a real estate investor, developer, and property entrepreneur. Slaven is heading groups of companies – Maximum Group Holdings and Ariobex Holdings Group. His motto with both groups is "Profit while doing good" and the groups have interests in the development of large-scale smart city human settlements (100 000 residents plus) and regional industrial and agricultural infrastructures. His groups of companies are also involved in utility- scale renewable energies, water treat

ment, smart metering, education, and so on. Maximum Group has an IT arm with interests in FinTech, AgriTech, cybersecurity, blockchains & smart payments platforms. Slaven is a founder of the Mega Projects Developers Association of South Africa and is well known in the Property Development and Real Estate investment circles. Hence, he enjoys a large network of professionals and megaproject development colleagues with whom he collaborates on a number of projects and aspects thereof. Slaven’s own “Conscious Property Alchemy” business model and unique RDP development model known as “RDP 2.0 – connected societies” is at the forefront of the industry. His ability to merge the "brick" and the "cloud" brings new efficiencies in planning property developments merged with cloud and IT technology in order to enable the 4th industrial revolution, Society 5.0 and RDP 2.0 Our vision is to be the leading catalyst for growth and investments in Africa. nd supports diverse talent acquisition. The Team: (1.Dr. Keitumetse Mothibeli [Chairperson]. Dr. Keitumetse Mothibeli has a vast experience in the field of Science, Research & Development, and is the current Chairperson of Hightower Petroleum Africa (HPA), an African - American Energy solutions company, the President of Oicitra Inc s’ SADC region division - a precious metals processing mining company headquartered in the United States and the Chairperson of Maximum Africa L.E.O an entrepreneurship platform aimed at bridging the gap between investors and high – potential vetted opportunities. She has assumed roles as the Chairperson of Crystal Partners, an investment company, the CEO of The Village Foundation, Research & Development Director for both Zucchi Innovations and Mofaya Beverage Company, and the Head of Research and Development at BMGLOBAL. She has tailored Monitoring and Evaluation systems, Compliance and Governance policies, Sales and Marketing Strategies for various bus

inesses. Her drive for entrepreneurship has seen her being appointed as a Limited Partner for a Side Equity Fund purposed at bridging the diaspora to opportunities in Africa. Through her entrepreneurial journey she has develop and successfully run Maidi Holdings, and become co- owner of Mr. Brick, a brick manufacturing company using green technology to solve brick manufacturing challenges. She has worked for Adcock Ingram and Zetland Technologies in partnership with the Council for Scientific and Industrial Research (CSIR) amongst other businesses. She has experience in the- Health, Energy, Infrastructure and Maritime sectors. Her passion lies in building and mentoring young and dynamic entrepreneurs into creating sustainable and meaningful businesses. She is a born leader and believes that sacrifice, commitment, consistency, excellence, integrity are characters that all good leaders should have and uphold. 2.
